---
description: Storybook-first UI workflow for reusable frontend changes.
globs: ["apps/miniapp/**", "apps/admin-web/**", "apps/shared-web/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Before modifying any reusable UI:
- inspect the relevant stories first
- treat stories as the contract
- do not patch page-local CSS if the issue belongs in the design system
- do not create a new component if an existing primitive, pattern, or layout can be extended
- do not consider the task complete until stories and tests are updated

For miniapp UI:
- Storybook is the source of truth for reusable UI behavior and state coverage
- **Story files**: place every `*.stories.tsx` under `apps/miniapp/src/stories/` only — design-system stories mirror `src/design-system/` under `src/stories/design-system/`; import components with `@/design-system/...`. Do not co-locate stories next to components. See `apps/miniapp/docs/storybook/AGENTS.md`.
- update `play` coverage when changing interactive behavior
- use realistic miniapp fixtures, not placeholder lorem or fake desktop layouts
